{
  "protocol": "morpho-v1",
  "description": "Morpho Blue (core lending) + MetaMorpho (vault layer) + periphery contracts across 35+ EVM chains",
  "lastUpdated": "2026-03-19",
  "notes": [
    "Morpho uses CREATE2 for deterministic deployment on some chains (e.g. Ethereum, Base share 0xBBBB... for Morpho core)",
    "Most chains have unique addresses for each contract due to different deployers or compilation flags",
    "V2 contracts (VaultV2Factory, MorphoRegistry) are the newer vault system",
    "V1 contracts (MetaMorpho Factory, Public Allocator) are the original Morpho Blue ecosystem",
    "Bundler3 and adapters vary per chain",
    "Source: docs.morpho.org/get-started/resources/addresses/ (llms-all.txt dump) + block explorer verification"
  ],
